@NODE M1 "What is MPLAYER"
@PREV Main
@NEXT M2






		WHAT IS MPLAYER?





	MPLAYER is a module player for MED modules.
	Though I know there are lot's of players for this
	purpose, but I wanted to make my own...





@ENDNODE

@NODE M2 "Requirements"
@PREV M1
@NEXT M3




		REQUIREMENTS:




	MPLAYER V2.0 needs at least KS2.0x and MEDPLAYER.LIBRRY
	in LIBS: directory to run.


	MPlayer has been created with A500, 0.5MB chip,
	2.5MB fast, KS3.1 and 120MB HD.



@ENDNODE

@NODE M3 "Installation"
@PREV M2
@NEXT M4



		INSTALLATION



	MPLAYER V2.0 is very easy to install. Just unpack
	MPLAYER20.lha into some directory and then copy
	MEDPLAYER.LIBRARY into LIBS:. (You find MEDPLAYER.LIBRARY
	in the medplayer/libs-directory)

	So there should be no problems....



@ENDNODE

@NODE M4 "Using MPLAYER"
@PREV M3
@NEXT M5



		Using MPLAYER V2.0



	When MPLAYER v2.0 is started first time, it asks
	module-dir. Then it opens the player-window.

	MPLAYER is capable for 150 modules, so look out...

	There are LOAD,PLAY,STOP.CONT,PREFS,ABOUT and INFO gadgets.

	After selecting the module from the LISTVIEW gadget, press
	the LOAD-button to load module. If nothing failed, just
	press the PLAY-button. Now there should be music..

	With the STOP-button playing stops, and you can continue
	playing with the CONT-button.

	PREFS-button allows you to change the module-dir. INFO-
	button gives you some info of the current module.

	ABOUT-button gives you some info about MPLAYER.


	MPLAYER v2.0 creates S:MPlayer.config to store the module 
	directory information.

	
@ENDNODE

@NODE M5 "Known bugs"
@PREV M4
@NEXT M6




		KNOWN BUGS:



	At this moment there is only one known bug:


	When MPLAYER v2.0 is run at the first time, it stops
	after asking the module directory... I'll try find
	what is causing this.

	But no worries, just run the MPLAYER v2.0 again...


@ENDNODE

